../../CHAIN-HISTORY.md:62:It deserves credit for the highest upside and for being tightly aligned with the mission's SQG blueprint. But even after refinement it still has a serious execution risk: algebraic reformulations are very good at looking nontrivial before they are tested against the actual localized estimate. The branch is improved by its estimate-first rewrite screen, yet it still has a materially weaker floor than Chain 01.
../../CHAIN-HISTORY.md:70:Its core problem is that the missing bridge is also the main difficulty: local near-Beltrami or alignment observables do not obviously control the full stretching quantity, especially the nonlocal remainder. That makes the branch valuable, but comparatively fragile. Its best negative result is useful, though still harder to secure cleanly than Chain 01's shell-based obstruction.
