../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:9:Its main weakness is that it quietly assumes any genuinely live beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism should appear as an immediate gain on one inherited localized bottleneck after an exact algebraic rewrite of the same quadratic nonlinearity. That is a very strong assumption, and it biases the chain toward proving that reformulations collapse back to the same obstruction. That outcome may be true, but the chain is structurally tilted toward it before the work begins.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:19:### 2. It assumes exact reformulation is a serious source of new leverage rather than mostly a change of presentation
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:21:For exact rewrites of NS, there is a default expectation: once one restores localization, projection, and commutator bookkeeping, the same quadratic structure reappears. The chain knows this, but still treats reformulation as a live discovery direction instead of treating "collapse back to the same estimate" as the generic baseline that must be defeated by a sharply identified mechanism.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:31:Step 3 is built to strip away gains that are "really" geometric or pressure-tensor effects. That is good if the goal is a pure reformulation result. It is bad if the only real NS-specific cancellations are hybrid: exact algebraic form plus alignment, or rewrite plus concentrated tube geometry, or rewrite plus tensor structure. The chain risks discarding the only live mechanisms because they are not pure enough.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:51:- It never says which bottleneck is mission-central. Is it the De Giorgi truncated pressure contribution, a local-energy flux term, a vorticity stretching localization, or some projected interaction? Those are not interchangeable. A rewrite that helps one may do nothing for the others.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:53:- The shortlist cap of at most three reformulations is efficient but arbitrary. If the screening criteria are vague, the cap mostly encodes prior taste, not mathematical evidence.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:58:### Step 2 - Test the shortlisted reformulations at the estimate level
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:64:- The natural test family is too familiar. Lamb-vector, projected form, and vorticity transport are exactly the rewrites one would expect to collapse back to the same structure unless some additional mechanism is injected. The mission context already suggests that at least part of this family has been effectively stress-tested.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:66:- The kill condition is close to tautological. Exact rewrites of the same quadratic nonlinearity generally do return the same Calderon-Zygmund or quadratic estimate once all costs are paid. If the chain only permits exact rewrites and treats that collapse as grounds for termination, then a negative result is the default, not a discovery.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:78:- It treats geometry, near-Beltrami structure, and tensor effects as things to subtract away before believing a gain. That is too purity-driven for this mission. The live beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism may be hybrid rather than purely algebraic.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:81:- The handoff logic is too clean. If a rewrite only helps when combined with local geometry, that may be evidence of the correct mechanism, not evidence that the reformulation chain failed.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:93:- The chain assumes that the main valuable positive output would be a closure criterion or theorem target. A sharp obstruction, rigidity statement, or clean no-go theorem for a reformulation family could be more realistic and more valuable.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:104:- If only a short list of familiar rewrites was tested, the negative claim must be very narrow. It cannot honestly become "exact reformulations do not help" without defining the family much more tightly.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:106:- The negative endpoint risks conflating "these few natural rewrites collapse" with "reformulation as a strategy is dead." The chain can support the former far more easily than the latter.
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:115:- it can close a specific loophole in the "maybe an exact rewrite creates an SQG-style gain" story;
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:116:- it can produce a bounded negative result on a tightly defined family of exact reformulations;
../../planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:122:2. that algebraic reformulation can be cleanly separated from geometry, tensor structure, or dynamics early enough that those can be treated mainly as contamination.
