../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right, but not all the way. The original chain is a credible branch if it is treated as a bounded obstruction test for exact-reformulation hopes inside one inherited estimate architecture. It is not credible as a primary discovery program for the mission's live beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:17:Still, that limitation is acceptable if the branch is labeled honestly. A cleanup test of the "maybe an exact rewrite helps inside the old architecture" loophole is worth running. What is not acceptable is advertising that cleanup branch as a broad search for the mission's hidden mechanism.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:19:### 2. The chain treats exact reformulation as too live a discovery direction instead of making obstruction the baseline
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:23:The attacker is right that exact rewrites of the same quadratic nonlinearity usually collapse back to the same localized costs once projection, commutators, and cutoffs are restored. The refined chain should therefore assume collapse is the baseline outcome unless a sharply identified mechanism defeats it.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:33:Without that discriminator, Step 1 can admit attractive but empty algebraic reformulations.
