../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:24:- The example identity `u . grad u = grad(|u|^2 / 2) - u x omega` is textbook. After projection, the gradient is removed and one is left with the Lamb-vector term. That does not by itself reduce derivative count or remove quadraticity; it just relocates them.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:25:- Helmholtz projection is order zero. It can expose cancellations, but it does not automatically transform a second-order CZ-type obstruction into a first-order gain. The step is written as though the right rewrite might make the problem "gain-bearing" by algebra alone. That is the main hidden assumption, and it is weak.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:26:- "Gain-bearing bilinear object" is undefined. Gain in what sense: one derivative, one power of integrability, a better level-set exponent, or a local-energy closure? Without pinning that down, Step 2 can bless aesthetically pleasing formulas that have no relevance to the `beta = 4/3` wall.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:27:- Scale counting is not enough. A symbol can look first-order under naive counting and still fail once the relevant truncation, commutator, or nonlocal pressure reconstruction is applied. This step needs estimate-level testing, not just identity-level algebra.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:36:- Testing exact Beltrami flows is a weak stress test for an allegedly generic NS mechanism. Exact Beltrami is a highly nongeneric symmetry class where the Lamb vector vanishes by design. Success there proves almost nothing.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:37:- The mission context already records the crucial negative fact: the Beltrami-based cancellation does not survive even very small perturbations from alignment. That means Step 3 is in danger of rediscovering an established fragility rather than testing a genuinely open point.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:38:- "Small perturbations away from Beltrami alignment" is underspecified. Small in `L^2`, `H^1`, direction field, or a pointwise angle deficit? These are mathematically very different. Without fixing the perturbation metric, the stress test is not interpretable.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:40:- This step overlaps heavily with Chain 03. Once the test object becomes "Beltrami alignment plus perturbations," the chain has drifted from algebraic reformulation into geometry-first fragility analysis. That weakens the claim that Chain 02 is meaningfully distinct.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:42:Concrete failure mode: Step 3 may produce an inequality that looks favorable in an exact or nearly exact Beltrami regime, then collapse outside that regime. At that point the chain has not found an SQG-type mechanism; it has merely recovered the known statement that special alignment depletes the nonlinearity.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The negative endpoint is too broad relative to the search procedure. "NS has no SQG-type first-order cancellation in any natural formulation tested here" is fair. Stronger language such as "no SQG-style commutator analogue survives the NS vector geometry" is not earned by checking a short list of familiar formulations.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:51:- The step also inherits the contamination from Step 3. If the surviving mechanism is really a near-Beltrami geometry effect, then the chain should close by handing that result to the geometry branch, not by presenting it as an algebraic reformulation win.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:53:Concrete failure mode: Step 4 can produce a memo that sounds definitive while the underlying work only ruled out a handful of obvious rewrites and one nongeneric Beltrami-based pilot.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:68:- Beltrami/Lamb-vector fragility is also already on record.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:69:- Once Step 3 uses Beltrami perturbations, the chain overlaps materially with Chain 03.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:77:- Step 3's kill condition is actually reasonable if the target is a generic NS mechanism, but then it makes the branch nearly predetermined because prior context already says Beltrami cancellation is highly fragile.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:84:The chain is visibly captivated by the SQG analogy. That is useful as a generator of questions, but it can also force NS into a mold that the mission context already says is structurally mismatched: scalar truncation, linear constitutive law, and first-order commutator structure. A fairer framing would be "does NS possess an alternative cancellation mechanism that plays an analogous strategic role?" not "can we find the NS version of the SQG commutator?"
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:100:If this chain is kept, it should be treated as a short obstruction-hunting branch, not a full four-step attack path. The honest version is: front-load the Tao filter, demand an estimate-level improvement by the end of Step 2, and stop immediately if the only surviving signal is Beltrami-alignment fragility, because that is geometry-branch material rather than an SQG-type algebraic breakthrough.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:19:- The proposed target quantities are also too easy to game. "Critical-norm transfer" or "stretching-facing spectral production" can be named without any prior reason to think they survive localization, time integration, or cancellation.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:20:- "Define in advance what would count as a usable gain" sounds disciplined, but at this stage it is fake discipline. A gain that looks usable before localization and norm conversion often disappears once commutators, phase loss, or packet overlap are included.
../../../../library/factual/INDEX.md:8:- `geometry-route-screening/`: reusable notes on prior-art overlap, Beltrami fragility, tube-persistence survival, and the narrowed Step-2 survivor list for the post-pressure geometry branch.
../../planning-runs/run-003/planner.md:27:Central premise: Step `step-001` killed generic harmonic-tail gains but left one narrow pressure-side survivor: exact pressure-Hessian and strain structure might still act on the remote-shell moments that generate the affine-or-higher harmonic tail, or on full stretching in a way generic CZ estimates do not see.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:1:# Attack on Chain 03 - Geometric Vorticity Alignment and Local Beltrami Tubes
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:- local Beltrami alignment (`u` nearly parallel to `omega`)
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The chosen observables do not naturally feed one another. Small local Beltrami deficit controls `u x omega`, but Constantin-Fefferman type criteria care about spatial regularity of the vorticity direction field. A flow can be pointwise near-Beltrami inside each tube core while `xi` varies wildly from tube to tube or even across nearby filaments.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:22:- The kill condition is too soft. The chain should die not only if known geometric criteria are "too nonlocal," but also if every bridge from local Beltrami deficit to those criteria passes through derivative control of `xi` or some comparably stronger hypothesis. That is not a technical nuisance. That is the obstruction.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:26:### Step 2 - Quantify depletion from local Beltrami structure
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The anchor case is pointed at the wrong object. Exact Beltrami structure annihilates the Lamb vector `u x omega`, but the dangerous term in the vorticity equation is vortex stretching, i.e. `(omega · grad)u = S omega`. Small `u x omega` does not by itself imply small `S omega` or small `S omega · omega`.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The step quietly assumes a perturbative principle that the mission context already warns against. Exact Beltrami cancellation is known to be extremely fragile. Localizing the condition to high-vorticity regions does not cure that fragility, because the strain and pressure are nonlocal.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:33:- "Using exact-Beltrami cancellation as the anchor case" risks importing De Giorgi/pressure intuition into a vorticity-stretching problem. The two phenomena are related only indirectly. This step needs a direct path from local alignment to control of `S omega`, not a memory of a different cancellation.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:36:The kill condition again fires too late. If the only estimate available is "local alignment controls a local piece of the stretching," that is already failure, because the unresolved nonlocal remainder is precisely the critical part.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:47:This step should be judged by a much stricter standard: does it create a genuinely new implication from local Beltrami geometry to a known regularity mechanism? If not, it should terminate as a negative result, not be upgraded into a "draft proposition."
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:60:- The chain conflates Beltrami alignment, vorticity-direction coherence, and tube persistence. They are related heuristically, not quantitatively. Treating them as one mechanism is the central structural flaw.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- The success criterion is too forgiving. "Conditional statement or conjecture" is cheap. The chain should count as success only if it proves a new scale-appropriate bridge from local Beltrami deficit to an existing regularity criterion, or else a rigorous obstruction showing why no such bridge exists.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- There is partial prior-art redundancy. Without a hard Beltrami-to-criterion bridge, the chain collapses back into known Constantin-Fefferman style regularity conditions plus suggestive tube language.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:78:- The bridge from local Beltrami structure to known geometric criteria is the whole problem, not a downstream detail.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:83:Treat it as a short obstruction hunt, not a long proof path. The first question should be whether any scale-critical estimate links local Beltrami deficit on high-`|omega|` sets to control of `S omega` or to a known vorticity-direction criterion. If the answer is no, the right output is a sharp fragility memo: local near-Beltrami geometry is a descriptive feature of vortex tubes, not an operational regularity lever.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/planner.md:27:Central premise: Step `step-001` killed generic harmonic-tail gains but left one narrow pressure-side survivor: exact pressure-Hessian and strain structure might still act on the remote-shell moments that generate the affine-or-higher harmonic tail, or on full stretching in a way generic CZ estimates do not see.
