../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:5:This chain is attacking the right high-upside question, but it is structurally at risk of confusing an algebraic rewrite with a usable estimate. The central analogy to SQG is weaker than the chain admits: in SQG, the first-order commutator is tied to scalar transport and a linear constitutive law, while in NS the Lamb-vector / vorticity / Helmholtz forms are mostly equivalent repackagings of the same quadratic vector interaction. Unless the chain screens candidates at the level of the actual localized or truncated estimate that matters, it can spend several steps rediscovering textbook identities and then either overclaim a negative result or drift into Chain 03's Beltrami geometry.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:13:- The hidden assumption is that a side-by-side comparison across velocity, vorticity, Lamb-vector, and Helmholtz-projected forms can reveal a genuinely new "slot" for SQG-style cancellation. That is not obvious. These are equivalent formulations before truncation/localization, and the mission-context obstruction is precisely that the bad behavior appears after truncation/localization.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:24:- The example identity `u . grad u = grad(|u|^2 / 2) - u x omega` is textbook. After projection, the gradient is removed and one is left with the Lamb-vector term. That does not by itself reduce derivative count or remove quadraticity; it just relocates them.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:25:- Helmholtz projection is order zero. It can expose cancellations, but it does not automatically transform a second-order CZ-type obstruction into a first-order gain. The step is written as though the right rewrite might make the problem "gain-bearing" by algebra alone. That is the main hidden assumption, and it is weak.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:36:- Testing exact Beltrami flows is a weak stress test for an allegedly generic NS mechanism. Exact Beltrami is a highly nongeneric symmetry class where the Lamb vector vanishes by design. Success there proves almost nothing.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The negative endpoint is too broad relative to the search procedure. "NS has no SQG-type first-order cancellation in any natural formulation tested here" is fair. Stronger language such as "no SQG-style commutator analogue survives the NS vector geometry" is not earned by checking a short list of familiar formulations.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The chosen observables do not naturally feed one another. Small local Beltrami deficit controls `u x omega`, but Constantin-Fefferman type criteria care about spatial regularity of the vorticity direction field. A flow can be pointwise near-Beltrami inside each tube core while `xi` varies wildly from tube to tube or even across nearby filaments.
../../planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The anchor case is pointed at the wrong object. Exact Beltrami structure annihilates the Lamb vector `u x omega`, but the dangerous term in the vorticity equation is vortex stretching, i.e. `(omega · grad)u = S omega`. Small `u x omega` does not by itself imply small `S omega` or small `S omega · omega`.
../../planning-runs/run-001/selector.md:12:- Chain 02 preserves the highest-upside path. It is the most direct attempt to turn the SQG blueprint into an NS-specific mechanism by testing whether the exact nonlinear algebra hides a first-order cancellation that Tao's averaged model destroys.
